    "name": "Korolevu Beach Serenaders",
    "profile": "The Korolevu Beach Serenaders appear to have evolved out of a Fiji-based trio of Tongan musicians, the Korolevu Serenaders Trio which consisted of Albert Bailey, George Tui'nukuafe (aka George Tui) and Paul Kaho. They were the resident a at the prestigious Korolevu Beach Resort. Later other members were to include [a5718954], [a4119876], Joe Logavatu and Pedro Philitoga, and reportedly, [url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/7185996-Henry-Purcell-2]Henry Purcell[/url].\r\n\r\nIn 1960, a single \"[r=11949448]\" was released on both the [l135787] and [l35333] labels. The members at the time were Albert Bailey, George Tui and Paul Kaho. In 1973. an LP [i][r=8995116][/i] was released on the [l112268] label. The LP cover indicated that there were six members which included a female. In 1976, another LP [i][r=19734670][/i] was released on [l28718]. The credited musicians were,  Ben Rausana - drums ; Gu Vananalagi - lead guitar, Pedro Philitoga - bass, Wilson Emberson - rhythm guitar and Theresa Purce",
